  "_about": "MEMEMAGE \u2014 This record is part of the Mememage provenance format for AI-generated images.\n\nBAR ENCODING: A 2-pixel-tall steganographic bar at the bottom of each image encodes a URL and content hash. The bar uses brightness-modulated pixels (bit 0 = avg brightness 64, bit 1 = avg brightness 192, threshold 128). Each bit spans 2 or 3 adjacent pixels (narrower images use 2, wider use 3). The bar is flanked by 8-pixel-wide Magenta/Yellow/Cyan color bands on each side as alignment markers. Frame format: [0xAD 0x4E magic][version byte][nsym][payload length BE 2B][CRC-16 2B][Reed-Solomon codeword]. Version 4 includes Reed-Solomon error correction (nsym parity bytes). The payload is UTF-8 text: the archive.org URL (without https:// prefix) followed by a null byte and a 16-character hex content hash.\n\nRESOLVE: Fetch https://archive.org/download/<identifier>/metadata.json or search archive.org for the identifier (e.g. mememage-a06b05c6cb1d). The identifier is 12 hex characters after the mememage- prefix.\n\nVERIFY: Compute SHA-256 of the canonical JSON (all keys sorted recursively, compact separators with no spaces, integer-valued floats normalized to integers, all fields except 'content_hash' and '_about'). The first 16 hex characters must match the 'content_hash' field.\n\nGPS TIME-LOCK: The born.gps_locked field contains RSA time-lock encrypted GPS coordinates. To decrypt: compute ct^(2^t) mod N, XOR the result with the ciphertext. At t=10^18 sequential squarings, this requires ~10 years of computation at current hardware speeds.\n\nDECODER CHAIN: The full decoder source code is embedded across 12 consecutive records in the chain (decoder_chunk fields, indexed 0-11). To reconstruct: collect all 12 chunks from one Age, sort by decoder_chunk_index, concatenate decoder_chunk values, base64 decode, gzip decompress. The result is a self-contained HTML file.\n\nAGES: Each set of 12 chunks constitutes an Age (version epoch). The decoder_age_name field identifies the epoch (e.g. Age of Aries). A new Age begins only after the previous Age completes its 12-chunk cycle."
